HEADWORD: Inconsequence
<hw>In*con"se*quence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inconsequentia</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>incons⟦eacute⟧quence</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of
being inconsequent; lack of just or logical inference or argument;
inconclusiveness.</def> <rj><au>Bp. Stillingfleet.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Strange, that you should not see the <qex>inconsequence</qex> of
your own reasoning!</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Hurd.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inconsequent</ent>⟦br⟧
